<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I was kindof disappointed in the net effect of that scene, but pleased by the use of the Witch King's Genuine Tolkien Lines.
<br />

<br />
In fact, overall, I was a little disappointed in the overall value of the new scenes in the extended edition overall.  Here's my blow by blow of the scenes I remember as being new (Since I don't have my DVD in front of me =P )
<br />

<br />
#1: The Demise of Sauruman - this scene actually worked really well.  A high density of GTLs on the part of both Saruman and Theoden provides some of the best dialogue in the film.  The unfolding of the events, while different from the book, captures the spirit pretty well.  Two thumbs up.
<br />

<br />
#2: Drinking contest between Legolas and Gimli.  Uh. Humorous, but doesn't really add anything.  Could've stayed gone, IMHO.  Gimli gets little enough respect as it is.  One Thumb down.
<br />

<br />
#3: Merry swears fealty to king Theoden - pretty good scene, though somehow didn't have the impact I expected. Seemed like a bit of a footnote. One thumb up.
<br />

<br />
#4: Pippin meets Faramir in Minas Tirith.  Heartwarming good character building moment.  Maybe a little slow, but I was glad to see it.  One thumb up.
<br />

<br />
#5: Eomer questions Merry's resolve to Eowyn.  Eh.  Not super compelling, but I liked that Eomer got to have a little more face time.  He and Theoden are the two characters from TTT/RotK that I felt were severely underutilized.   No thumbs either way.
<br />

<br />
#6: Gate of Minas Tirith resists sissy orcish battering ram.  Good scene.   Builds up the strength of the Minas Tirith a bit in the eyes on the audience so it doesn't seem so easy.  Makes Grond's later appearance more impressive.  One thumb up.
<br />

<br />
#7: Extended Paths of the Dead w/ghosty hands and skull-a-lanche.  What is this CRAP?  I'm glad to see someone reigned in Peter Jackson's bad horror movie instincts and got this stuff cut from the theatrical, but I wish they'd held out and kept it out of the extended too. (Exception: Legolas quoting the prophecy of the dead on the way to the door really worked nicely.  The sequence only goes down the toilet after they go inside.)  Two Thumbs down.
<br />

<br />
#8: Army of the Dead vs the Corsairs of Umbar - not bad. Explains WTF Aragorn and company were doing on the boats, though diminishes the already weak surprise of the Army of the Dead saving the day at Minas Tirith.  Probably could have stayed gone.  One Thumb down.
<br />

<br />
#9: Eowyn vs Gothmog (aka "Puffy Bloated Orc").  Unnecessary at best.   Especially since it's Aragorn, who, of everyone in the film, is the one who -least- needs to prove his badassness, who eventually gets the kill shot. (Though Kudos to Gimli for getting a good lick in.);  Would much rather Gothy had be axed by Eomer or Theoden, neither of who get to do much of anything really heroic. (Okay, Eomer dispatches the first Mumakil with his giant elephant collision trick, but still.)  I was annoyed by this scene.  One Thumb down.
<br />

<br />
#10: Gandalf vs The Witch King.  Makes Gandalf look kinda lame, really.  Good Tolkien lines on the part of the Witch King, but would much rather this scene had gone closer to the book.  Being generous her and giving this scene no thumbs. =P
<br />

<br />
#11: Houses of Healing.  Good scene. Nicely done.  Two thumbs up.
<br />

<br />
#12: Aragorn challenges Sauron in the Palantir.  Good idea, very questionable implementation (Rather like the Witch King vs Gandalf scene).  I remain totally confused about WTF happens with the Evenstar pendant, since it seems like Aragorn drops it, but he wasn't actually -holding- it as far as I can tell, having the Palantir in one hand and Anduril in the other.   Would have worked better closer to the book.  One thumb down.
<br />

<br />
#13: The Mouth of Sauron. Kinda freaky looking, but doesn't really -work- as a scene.  Having Aragorn decapitate him at the end was a bad decision too. One thumb down.
<br />

<br />
Total thumbs: 7 up, 7 down.  That's not a good wash for an extended cut.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
